content:
Call Center integrates Salesforce with third-party computer-telephony integration (CTI) systems. Call center users can see Salesforce information for incoming calls, make out-going calls directly from Salesforce, and report on call outcome, duration, and more.

A call center is great for boosting productivity for Salesforce users that spend time on the phone.

Available in: Essentials, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

To set up a call center, work with a developer or partner to create a CTI implementation that uses the Open CTI API and works with your existing telephony system. Most call centers are created by installing an AppExchange package.

After a call center is set up, call center users can make and receive calls with a softphone. Each softphone looks and behaves differently because each CTI implementation is unique.

The call center is all about customization. You can modify softphone layouts and assign specific layouts to selected user profiles.
title: Setting Up Salesforce Call Centers
